  <span id="freeText6928651177081978494" style="display:none">I enjoyed the subject matter, the historical setting, and above all, Buechner's writing style. He has a way of capturing the Christian-incarnate spiritual longing, as it is obstructed by carnality. He's not focused on theological accuracy as much as spiritual experience, which is very interesting to read though can be at times a little disconcerting. <br /><br />Someone recommended this book to me because they could tell it's exactly the sort of book I'd enjoy. In a lot of ways, it is, but for some reason I'm left a bit confused by what I read. And so, I can't entirely recommend. I think I'll need to read a bit more Buechner. </span>
